  "prompt": "Do VoLTE calls work with data switched off?",
  "response": "Yes, VoLTE (Voice over LTE) calls can work with mobile data switched off. VoLTE is a technology that enables high-quality voice calls over a 4G LTE network rather than the traditional 2G or 3G networks. When making a VoLTE call, the voice data is transmitted over the LTE network, but this doesn't require your mobile data to be turned on. The separation between data and voice channels in LTE allows for this functionality. Therefore, you can make and receive VoLTE calls even if the mobile data is disabled on your device.",
